Miss South Africa runner-up Sasha-Lee Olivier will represent the country at Miss World 2019. JOHANNESBURG - The Miss World 2019 beauty pageant broadcast time has changed and will now be aired from 17h00 on Saturday, 14 December 2019 on SABC 3. The Miss South Africa organisation confirmed the time change for the pageant, which was originally meant to be broadcast at 15h00, on Twitter. WATCH: Sasha-Lee to represent SA at Miss World 2019 "Miss World broadcast change. Please note that the Miss World 2019 competition airing time has been moved to 5pm on @SABC3", read the post. Miss South Africa runner-up Sasha-Lee Olivier will represent the country at the pageant.